00:19:53,460 --> 00:19:57,100
 and going and not slowing down because we know that if we stop pushing ourselves and

301
00:19:57,100 --> 00:20:02,420
 if we slow down, people might see what's truly inside.

302
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:09,260
 Jesus in his love and in his tenderness just says, "Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting

303
00:20:09,260 --> 00:20:10,820
 me?"

304
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:12,920
 Take a moment to think about what it is you're doing.

305
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:18,380
 What is deep inside of you that is driving you to do this very thing?

306
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:21,340
 I love the fact that he says, "Saul, Saul."

307
00:20:21,340 --> 00:20:23,180
 It's a tender thing.

308
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:28,440
 It's almost like Jesus is saying with his name twice, "I really know you.

309
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,620
 Like I understand you.

310
00:20:29,620 --> 00:20:30,740
 I see you.

311
00:20:30,740 --> 00:20:32,580
 I know what's going on in your heart.

312
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:34,540
 I know the things that you wrestle with.

313
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:36,780
 I know the insecurities that sit there.

314
00:20:36,780 --> 00:20:39,340
 I know why it is that you seem to be so driven.

315
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:43,260
 I know the selfishness and the jealousy and the anger and the hurt.

316
00:20:43,260 --> 00:20:47,140
 I can see it all inside of you, but none of it repulses me.

